[conversation_banth]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I see you carry the mark of the Utraean Society. I sure hope that you can save us for we cannot save ourselves. If what the Priests are saying is true then a better future does indeed wait for us all. However the omens haven't been good for this blizzard first swept in the day after the announcement of the reunification of the Stones. While the weather has always been harsh here in Fallraen, we have always been able to cope for the weather is usually benign at this time of the year and the ground rich and fertile. This year however we no sooner planted the first spring crops then the Blizzard struck and hasn't abated. That in itself is unusual for the mountain updraughts usually result in quick changes in weather extremes. Now however it's been 6 weeks without a break. The crops have perished and the stores dangerously low. If no supplies reach us soon I afraid it'll be too late.";
	}
}
[conversation_tiaend]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Now that you say the road to Crystwind is clear, I doubt that many people will stay in this wretched town. When the Utraean Priests announced that they were going to reunite the Townstones, all of our heads were filled with visions of what that would mean. Neverending spring weather, bountiful crops throughout the year and plenty for all. Instead the next day this unseasonal Blizzard swept in and destroyed the first spring crops. Now we are facing a famine instead of a feast and the visions of a better future is but a distant memory.";
	}
}
[conversation_kelran]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I'm impressed! You've sure have more guts than the rest of us yellow bellies around here. While we huddle around like turkeys on thanksgiving day, you're actually trying to achieve something! I'd love to join you but I'm afraid that I'd just be a hindrance. This perpetual cold has sapped my will and now I'm just like the rest of them.";
	}
}
[conversation_lyetia]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "I've lived here for 20 years and I've never seen a Summer like this one. Normally by now there'd be wildflowers & birds everywhere by now by nothing can grow with all of this snow around. Everything is withering with frostbite and monsters assault the Town gates every night.";
	}
}
[conversation_hasuf]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Talk about being frozen alive! I'm trying my best to stay warm but it's not working. No matter where you go you're freezing to death. Now if reuniting these Stones that the Priests are talking about would really stop this blizzard, while I'd even risk my life to help find them. Not that I believe a thing they say, after all they were saying about how Azunai has granted us a mild winter on the day they asked for adventurers to start looking for the Stones. The next day this blizzard swept in and has kept at it ever since.";
	}
}
[conversation_kalito]
{
	[text*]
	{
		screen_text = "Damn this freezing blizzard, it's giving me chill blains. If it doesn't stop soon, we're all going to freeze. To think that everyone was so excited about the announcement from the Utraean Priests that they were looking to reunite the Stones of Utrae! Then the next day the blizzard started and nobody's been able to spare the time to start looking for the Stones.";
	}
}
[conversation_eloeta]
{
	[text*]
	{
		button_1_text = "Directions";
		button_1_value = d_0x02700265;
		screen_text = "Welcome to the Fallraen Heights Tavern. I'm afraid that all we can serve you is Varg cutlets or Yeti dumplings, washed down with ice cold Iceflow cider. The last few months have been hell, if you excuse the pun. Ever since this unseasonal blizzard has hit us and cut off the supply routes, things have been tough. With the patrols unable to go far, the monsters have taken up residence just outside the town gates, as you very well know since you're managed to thin their numbers down somewhat. For which I gratefully thank you. Maybe we may get some fresh supplies in now?";
	}
}
